Tickets for the 2021 TotalEnergies Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) officially started yesterday. This is according to a communiqué signed by Narcisse Mouelle Kombi, Minister of Sports and Physical Education and President of the AFCON Local Organising Committee better known by its French acronym COCAN. The communiqué made public the different sales points found in the different sites with priority given to councils of the host towns.   Djokovic  gets Covid-19 exemption for Aussies     AFCON 2021: 23 players in Super Eagles camp as Iheanacho,…     Super Eagles get Sudan warning   The sales points, as per the communiqué, are opened as from 8 a.m. to 8 p.m. throughout the competition. - Advertisement - The communiqué also revealed the prices which range from FCFA 3,000 to FCFA 20,000 depending on the category and the stage of the competition.